        <!-- <section>
            <h>object</h>
            <p><g>bocsa</g> can be the object of certain <a href="?xx=prepositions/prepositions"
                    >prepositions</a>.</p>-->
            <p><g><a href="?gd=ugh">ugh</a> ann am bocsa</g>
                <en>an egg in a box</en> – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Dé tha anns a’ bhocsa sin? Tha uighean anns a’ bhocsa.</gd>
                        <tr>What is in that box? There are eggs in the box.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 20</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
            <p><g><a href="?gd=leabhar">leabhar</a> ann am bocsa</g>
                <en>a book in a box</en> – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Nach robh leabhar anns a’ bhocsa sin? Bha. Bha Bìobull ann.</gd>
                        <tr>Wasn’t there a book in that box? Yes, there was. There was a Bible (in
                            it).</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 20</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
            <p><g><a href="?gd=biiobull">Bìobull</a> ann am bocsa</g>
                <en>a Bible in a box</en> – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Nach robh leabhar anns a’ bhocsa sin? Bha. Bha Bìobull ann.</gd>
                        <tr>Wasn’t there a book in that box? Yes, there was. There was a Bible (in
                            it).</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 20</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
